{"experiments":{"api-version":3,"api-revision":"091015","version":3.0,"revision":"091015","total":1,"total-samples":8,"total-assays":8,"experiment":[{"id":167272,"accession":"E-MEXP-98","name":"Transcription profiling by array of Arabidopsis mutant for hsf1 and hsf3 after heat shock treatment","releasedate":"2004-12-15","lastupdatedate":"2014-05-03","organism":["Arabidopsis thaliana"],"experimenttype":["transcription profiling by array"],"experimentdesign":["stimulus or stress"],"description":[{"id":null,"text":"The aim of the expression profiling was to define and to apply criteria that allow discrimination between the effects of heat stress (HS) and HSF-dependent gene expression in Arabidopsis. Therefore we determined and analyzed the expression profiles of wild type (WT) and homozygous hsf1--\/hsf3-- double knock out mutant plants (abbreviated hsf1\/3). Hsf1\/3 plants are deficient in HSF1 and HSF3 activity and unable to induce the fast transient expression of mRNAs of a number of HS genes tested (Lohmann et al., 2004).<br><\/br> The effects of HS on gene expression were analyzed after one hour heat treatment (37C) of leaf tissue."}],"provider":[{"contact":"Wolfgang Busch","role":"submitter","email":"wolfgang.busch@student.uni-tuebingen.de"}],"bibliography":[{"accession":15610345,"authors":"Busch W, Wunderlich M, Sch√∂ffl F.","title":"Identification of novel Heat Shock Factor dependent genes and biochemical pathways in Arabidopsis thaliana","doi":"10.1111\/j.1365-313X.2004.02272.x","status":"published"}],"samplecharacteristic":[{"category":"Age","value":[38]},{"category":"BioSourceType","value":["frozen_sample"]},{"category":"DevelopmentalStage","value":["6.30 Boyes key"]},{"category":"Ecotype","value":["Wassilewskija"]},{"category":"GeneticModification","value":["gene_knock_out","none"]},{"category":"Genotype","value":["hsf1--\/hsf3--","wild_type"]},{"category":"Individual","value":["1x3 HS I (5)","1x3 HS II (1)","1x3 RT I (7)","1x3 RT II (3)","WS HS I (6)","WS 